---
source: crates/kul-wasm/tests/format.rs
expression: formatted
---
# Example 8: Clean divorce, remarriage, and child-anchoring ghosts (P8).
#
# - Alice and Bob marry in 1972 and have a daughter Carol.
# - The marriage ends in divorce in 1990.
# - Alice later marries Charlie in 1995 and they have a daughter Diana.
# - Bob later marries Eva in 1992 and they have a son Felix.
#
# This is the canonical workout for P8's child-anchoring ghosts:
# Alice's and Bob's canonical cards live at their respective current
# intimacies (m_alice_charlie and m_bob_eva). At their past marriage
# m_alice_bob, both Alice and Bob render as ghosts so Carol's birth
# edge has an anchor. Carol's canonical card sits in the m_alice_bob
# children row — she is unaffected by her parents' subsequent moves.

# ---- Generation 1 (founders, no birth families) ----
person alice    name:"Alice Reyes"   gender:female  born:1950-04-12
person bob      name:"Bob Singh"     gender:male    born:1948-11-30
person charlie  name:"Charlie Park"  gender:male    born:1949-02-22
person eva      name:"Eva Larsen"    gender:female  born:1953-08-04

# ---- First marriage: Alice + Bob, ended ----
marriage m_alice_bob alice bob  start:1972-05-12  end:1990-08-01  end_reason:divorce

# ---- Generation 2: Carol (bio child of the ended marriage) ----
person carol  name:"Carol Singh"  gender:female  born:1975-09-03
  birth m_alice_bob

# ---- Remarriages ----
marriage m_bob_eva       bob   eva      start:1992-06-15
marriage m_alice_charlie alice charlie  start:1995-10-20

# ---- Generation 2: children of the remarriages ----
person felix  name:"Felix Singh"  gender:male    born:1994-03-11
  birth m_bob_eva
person diana  name:"Diana Park"   gender:female  born:1997-07-29
  birth m_alice_charlie
